        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 5:26PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 525 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of La Veta Pass, or 33 miles east of San Luis Valley
Airport, moving northwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, penny size hail and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Spring Burn Scar south of Highway 160 in Costilla county, Indian
Creek on the southeastern Spring Burn Scar, and western Spring Burn
Scar south of Highway 160 in Huerfano county.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
